The Governing Council, Federal Polytechnic, Oko, Anambra State has approved the appointment of Mr. Umeozor Anthony Ogochukwu as the substantive registrar of the polytechnic The approval, according to a statement by the Acting Public Relations Officer, Chijioke Ibeziako, was made at the council’s emergency meeting held on June 23. “The selection board committee of the council had earlier conducted interview for the position of Registrar and forwarded their recommendations to the council. “Mr. Ogochukwu, who hails from Uga in Anambra State, has been a Deputy Registrar in the Polytechnic for 15 years. He has held positions at different capacities in the polytechnic.   Don lauds Babatope, Oyetola for Ilesa university     FESTAC Grammar School, Command Day, others shine at Brain…     New curriculum for overage out-of-school children adopted   “He is a holder of M.Ed (Education) and is a Member of Nigeria Institute of Management (MNIM). He takes over from Mrs. Ifeoma Ezeokoli , who is on acting capacity,” the statement reads. The Council Chairman, Malam Kale Kawu, expressed satisfaction at the process leading to the Registrar’s emergence, just as he hailed the selection board committee for discharging their task with tact and dedication. Describing registry department as  the engine room of the polytechnic, Kawu urged the new registrar to bring his wealth of experience to bear in his new assignment and add great value to the polytechnic. He called for co-operation and support for the registrar from the management and members of staff.